OL,3,C'Disbelief' of parish councillor
OL,4,Cassaulted in row over trees
OL,6,FRichard Wright KC, defending, said his
OL,7,Fclient had "learned a salutary lesson"
OL,8,Fand told the court he had made a
OL,9,F"massive contribution to the GDP of
OL,10,Fthe UK".
OL,12,FMr Wright said Makin was "used to
OL,13,Fgetting on with things and getting a
OL,14,Fjob done in the public interest".
OL,16,F"He wanted to get this job done but
OL,17,Fwent about it the wrong way," he added.
OL,19,FMakin, from Micklefield in North
OL,20,FYorkshire, was fined #4,800 for
OL,21,Fassault by beating.
